We'll use the "MagicTelescope" dataset. The data is generated to simulate registration of high energy gamma particles. The TARGET column has values either:

  • g - gamma (signal) - we'll denote by 0,
  • h - hadron (background) - we'll denote by 1.

We'll also shuffle the data, just in case, to remove any potential bias encoded in the data order.
